args: ...Not a trace of life, as I feared.\nFie, but this is the fourth sudden\ndisappearance of a noble family.

All of them were pious followers of Ilia
who had donated large sums to the
Church. There is no possible reason
for them to flee or go into hiding.
Eeeeek! Please, no! Don't kill me!
Ah! Are you of this house, sir?\nIf so, might you inform me as to\nwhat happened here, if anything?
D-don't come near me! You're a Paladyn—\nyou're friends with HER!
Pray, sir, calm yourself and tell me\nwhat has transpired here.
A sylvan woman...used a-arrows...\nThe mirror! Everyone...in despair...\nNoooo, I don't want to die!
She's still near! She must be!

I was curious to see how the youngest
Grand Paladyn in history had grown.
Alas, I find you to be naught more
than a hopeless disappointment.
Yes. She was once a Paladyn who\nserved the Goddess Ilia.
Long before I was a Paladyn for true,\nshe taught me of their comportments\nand martial arts.
We weren't so close as to have been\nteacher and pupil—but she was one of\nthe Paladyns I aspired to be like.

And how long it has been, Elisanne?
Ah, I did not wish to see you again,
yet as this presents an opportunity to
end your life, I cannot complain of it.
I heard you were excommunicated just\nas I was promoted to the rank of Paladyn.
But does this mean the disappearances\nof the Ilian faithful are your doing?
I despair for your faculties that you even\nfeel the need to pose such a query.
I won't let it stand if you\nkilled the people here!

Your proclivity for taking up the mantle of
a knight in shining armor is repugnant,
seventh scion. But I suppose it's no
surprise from a puppet.
Puppet? What is that supposed to—
Do you truly think I will answer every\nfool query you think to toss my direction?\nHow terrifically naive.
You were once a splendid Paladyn\nwith an ironclad sense of justice.

You went too far at times, true, but we all
still respected you—nay, even sought to
BE you. How can you have turned to
such violent actions in the meantime?
Your memory is despairingly weak.\nAnd further, you misunderstand.
I have not changed at all—I still act to\nprotect justice and order. I have simply\ncome to a new realization.
I now recognize the deception that the\nIlian Church spreads across this world.
Your lack of understanding is further proof\nthat you Paladyns yet cling to false justice.
The righteousness and justice that you tout\nis nothing more than convenient dogma.
The notion of universal equity is mere\nself-righteousness; the idea of a just\nworld is but mistaken presumption.

Sinners float above this world awash in
material possessions and glory while
the good and pure die languishing in
gutters. THIS is the truth of the world.

The doctrine of the Ilian Church averts its
eyes from reality, preferring instead the
false promise of salvation. Then they deign
call obedience of that doctrine ＂order.＂

But however splendid the words one uses
to hide the truth, people will still kill one
another without hesitation if it means
their own survival.

You brandish that lance at me and call
it justice, but it is nothing more than a
means to justify your own violent ends.
I despair for you, Paladyn. Truly I do.

You poor, pitiful child. You have been
cowed by putrid deception, unable to even
question the false justice to which you
cling so very fiercely.
Thus will I release you from that false\njustice, for I cannot ignore the plaintive\nwails of such a pitiful child.
And how many lives have you ended\nusing that selfsame reasoning?

They lacked tenacity, and so went
without salvation. Pain will later
lead to happiness. These are the
lies that hide the despair of reality.

The absence of salvation? Suffering?
All of it is meaningless. This is the
cruel yoke of our reality, and a lesson
I made certain to teach them well.
How can you stand there and call\nANY of this salvation?!
Poor, pitiful Elisanne. It seems you\nalso wish to avert your gaze from\nthe cruel nature of reality.

I understand, for I was once very much
the same. But you must accept despair,
which means the time has come for me
to liberate you from ＂justice.＂
That is no liberation! You may have\ntossed your faith aside, but I refuse\nto do the same!

If you choose to wallow in base despair,
you must do it alone. For no matter how
cruel the world might be, I will hold fast
to the order and righteousness I believe in!
As Grand Paladyn of the Ilian Church,\nI will end your atrocities this day!
The depths of your naivety are staggering.
But I will wrest you free of the deception\nyou cling to! ...Feral Shroud, expand!
This barrier... You're one of them!
We are wings of judgment which unfurl in\nrejection of the deceit of this world!\nWe are AGITO!
I will thrust you into the depths of despair!
